  "prompt": "How does a person's life change by becoming a nun?",
  "response": "Becoming a nun involves significant lifestyle changes:\n\n1. Spiritual Commitment\n- Dedicating life to religious service\n- Taking vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience\n- Deepening personal faith and spiritual practices\n\n2. Lifestyle Changes\n- Living in a convent or monastery\n- Following strict daily schedules and routines\n- Wearing religious habits\n- Limited personal possessions\n- Communal living with other nuns\n\n3. Personal Relationships\n- Typically remaining celibate\n- Reduced contact with family and outside world\n- Forming close relationships within religious community\n- Focusing on spiritual connections\n\n4. Career and Work\n- Dedicating time to prayer and religious service\n- Often working in areas like education, healthcare, or social services\n- Potential missionary work\n- Community service and charitable activities\n\n5. Personal Identity\n- Adopting a new name\n- Prioritizing spiritual growth\n- Commitment to religious principles\n- Simplified lifestyle\n- Emphasis on community and collective goals\n\n6. Daily Routine\n- Regular prayer and meditation\n- Structured communal activities\n- Limited personal free time\n- Disciplined and contemplative lifestyle\n\nEach religious order has unique specific practices, but these are general characteristics of becoming a nun.",
